gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 140, Pacers 126
gameRecap.excerpt: Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded a new career-high 64 points as the Bucks defeated the Pacers, 140-126. Giannis added 14 rebounds and four steals for the Bucks, with Damian Lillard adding 21 points and six assists in the victory. Tyrese Haliburton tallied 22 points, seven assists, and five rebounds for the Pacers in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 17-7 in the regular season, while the Pacers fall to 13-9.
